Business Intelligence/Data Analyst		Handy HQ		New York City, NY, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Overview<br /><br /></strong>We&rsquo;re a seeking a Business Intelligence/Data Analyst to join one of New York&rsquo;s fastest growing companies. You&rsquo;ll be working in a fast-paced, fun environment where you will have a tremendous impact on daily operations and develop insights for long term strategy. The ideal candidate is a curious and intelligent individual who loves to leverage data and is up for revolutionizing the way people buy home services.<br />As a Data Analyst you will: <ul> <li>Build business reports that will enable business teams to make impactful decisions.</li> <li>Audit and develop key performance indicators to identify and monitor business trends and growth opportunities.</li> <li>Conduct internal analyses to increase understanding and transparency of the business.</li> <li>Work with business teams to support various ongoing projects, including executive reporting, financial auditing, user retention strategies, supply &amp; demand acquisition.</li> <br /><br /></ul>Skills &amp; Requirements:<br /><ul> <li>A minimum of a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a business or quantitative discipline.</li> <li>2+ years experience within a competitive intelligence, business intelligence, or financial planning and analytics unit.</li> <li>2+ years experience with relational databases and languages used for querying (e.g. SQL, Hive).</li> <li>Advanced knowledge manipulating large data sets using BI reporting tools (e.g. Looker, Tableau, SAS).</li> <li>Advanced Excel skills including pivot tables, graphing and general advanced functions.</li> <li>Advanced researching skills to gather information from databases and multiple sources.</li> <li>A passion for data analysis that helps to drive business insights and decisions.</li> <li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills.</li> <li>R, Python and similar tools are a plus.</li> <br /><br /></ul>Compensation and Benefits: <ul> <li>Competitive salary, bonuses, and equity</li> <li>Health coverage</li> <li>Daily team lunches and dinners, frequent happy hours and team outings</li> <li>A fun office in the heart of Manhattan, always stocked with coffee, snacks, and other drinks</li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>About Handy<br /><br /></strong>Handy was started in 2012 by Oisin Hanrahan &amp; Umang Dua while at Harvard Business School. Featured on The New York Times and Forbes, Handy has raised $60 million from top-tier investors including Revolution Capital, Highland Capital and General Catalyst, who have invested in businesses like Airbnb and Kayak. Every day, in all major US cities and several locations in Canada and Europe, we connect our customers with great home service professionals. Our headquarters is located right on the border of Chelsea and Flatiron.<br /><br /></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Handy is the leading platform for connecting individuals looking for household services with top-quality, pre-screened independent service professionals. From home cleaning to handyman services, Handy instantly matches thousands of customers every week with trusted professionals in cities all around the world. With a seamless 60-second booking process, secure payment, and a 100% money-back guarantee, Handy is the easiest, most convenient way to book home services.</div>